Commentary.Commentary: The Windies now have to put all of that behind and bat well and show some fight. The Kiwis will probably want to do what they did in the first game. Can they? We will find out in a bit.

The Windies were initially good with the ball but lose intensity as the day went on. To add to that, their fielding was extremely poor and thay have probably dropped around 5 catches in totality. Chemar and Gabriel were probably the pick. Overall though, they will be very disappointed with their effort after electing to bowl.

End of a wonderful batting performance from the Kiwis! They will very pleased as to where they stand in the game after the first innings. Nicholls is the star for them. He was the mainstay and the others player around him. He had handy partnerships with Mitchell, Young and with Wagner. The one with Neil was the probably the one which frustrated the Windies the most and due to those stands, they have gotten to a formidable tota.
OUT! TAKEN! There is the end of the innings! Boult steps out and looks to hit it over mid-wicket but Brooks there dive to his right and takes a lovely catch! NEW ZEALAND ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 460!
Fires this outside off, it is played to covers.
SIX! That is some way to get off the mark! Boult steps down the track and heaves this over the mid-wicket fence. He will probably have some fun.

OUT! TAKEN! There is the end of Nicholls! A superb knock from him comes to an end! The Windies finally hang onto one he hits in the air towards their fielder. It is fuller and outside off. Nicholls hits it uppishly towards extra cover. Brathwaite there takes it. Nicholls walks off to a standing ovation and the Windies will hope the last wicket does not frustrate them for long.
One more single as this is worked towards fine leg for one more.
This is eased down to long on for one.
SIX! Pulled for a biggie again! This is short and on middle. Wagner stays back and pulls it over the square leg fence for a biggie.
Short and outside off, this is guided through point for one.
Outside off again, not played at.
FOUR! Hammered! Short and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked.
One more single as this is worked with the angle through mid-wicket.
Quicker and on middle, Chase keeps it out.
Wagner now takes one as this is pushed down to long on.
A single as thisis hit down to long on.
Angled into the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for two.
On middle, blocked.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! This is short and well outside off, Wagner cuts again. It goes over point and it races away to the fence again.;
FOUR! Shorter and outside off, Wagner slaps it over covers and bags another boundary.
Outside off, left alone.

Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for a couple. FIRST FIFTY FOR WAGNER! A very entertaining knock from him. He has had his share of luck but he has been brave in this knock. Went for his shots right from the word go and nailed quite a few of them.
Three! Fuller and on middle, this is worked through mid-wicket and three runs taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Once again Chase attacks the stumps. Blocked.
Fires it on middle. Wagner is solid in defense.
A single as this is eased down to long off.
Fires it on middle, it is kept out nicely.
On middle, blocked.
On the stumps to begin with, Nicholls blocks it nicely.
New Zealand on the other hand, will probably continue in the same vein and hope to get to the 450-run mark. Will they do so? We will find out. Join us in a bit.

The Windies were decent with the ball but it is their fielding once again which has been poor! Around three or maybe four dropped catches and that is probably the reason they are well behind in the game. They would really hope the Lunch break turns things around for them and they could end the Kiwi innings quickly and walk out to bat.

Another excellent session for New Zealand! They have managed to score over 100 runs and most of that is thanks to Wagner. After they lost Jamieson and Southee in quick succession, Wagner and Latham joined association. The former went after the bowlers and in no time has gotten close to a half ton. Nicholls on the other hand, is going along his own pace and the Kiwis are pretty close to positng a formidable total.
BEATEN! Length and around off, angled away. Wagner looks to defend but is beaten.
Shorter and outside off, Wagner looks to pull but misses.
On middle, defended.
Oh my says Wagner after playing it! Short and on middle, Wagner looks to pull but it goes off the top edge and lands safe in the third man region for two. Highest score for Wagner in Tests.
Well fielded by Campbell! On middle, this is worked towards wide mid on. John there dives to his left and stops it.
Outside off, this is guided through point for one.
On the stumps, another rare defensive stroke yb Wagner.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
On middle, kept out.
Worked with the angle through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Roston Chase is on now!
Length and around off, takes off again. Wagner is beaten as he looks to put bat on ball.
SIX! Into the crowd! This is brilliant from Wagner! Total entertainment for the crowd! It is short and on the body, Wagner plays the hook shot and nails it. Flies over the fine leg fence.
That took off! Shorter and around off, Wagner initially looks to cut but then due to the extra bounce, he is beaten.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
FOUR! The fifty run stand is up! An entertaining one and anotehr one which continues to frustrate the Windies. Shorter and on the body, this is pulled down to the fine leg fence.
Angled away from the off pole, Nicholls looks to defend but is beaten.
FOUR! More runs! Frustrating runs for the Windies! Outside off, this is carved down to third man for one boundary.
Length now and this is defended.
TOP EDGE AND FOUR! Not where Wagner intended but he won't care! It is short and on the body. Wagner looks to pull but it goes off the top edge to the third man fence. 400 up for New Zealand.
SIX! CRACKED! The sound that made of the bat was amazing! Shorter and around middle, Wagner pulls it hard and over the mid-wicket fence.
Shorter and outside off, Wagner looks to pull but misses.

FOUR! Through the hands! Another drop! This one is a tough! It is short and on te body. Wagner pulls again. It goes towards fine leg. Chase dives to his left and gets two hands to it but can't hold on. It goes for a boundary.
Shorter and on the body, this is worked towards square leg for one.

PUT DOWN! Once again! This is short and on the body, Wagner pulls it uppishly towards fine leg. Joseph runs in and looks to take it with a dive forward but drops it. The catching has been really poor from the Windies.
BEATEN! Shorter and outside off, Wagner goes after it but does not connect.
Down the leg side, Wagner looks to flick but misses.
150 for Nicholls, he is looking to make it as big as he can. Shorter and outside off, it is guided through point for one.
On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for two. Nicholls moves onto 149.
Shannon Gabriel is back on!
The physio is out to have a look but Wagner seems fine. This though is mandatory now a days. Wagner wants the helmet to be changed.
Goes short again, Wagner takes his eyes off the ball as he tries to pull but misses to get hit on the helmet.
Once again, right off the middle but finds the man at mid off.
FOUR! This is probably the best shot Wagner has played so far! It is fuller this time and on off, Wagner creams it through covers. No chance of stoppnig that.
Short again, Wagner looks to pull but misses to get hit on the arm.
SIX! Top edge and it goes all the way! Fortune favors the brave and it goes Wagner here. Short again, Wagner goes for the pull. It flies off the top edge and over the fine leg fence.
Shorter again, this is pulled through square leg for one.
FOUR! BANG! This one is smashed! It is slightly short and on off, Wagner pulls it hard and over mid-wicket for another boundary.
Once again plays the pull shot, not on control towards mid-wicket for two.
FOUR! Top edge and a boundary! Wagner is going to take on the challenge of pulling. Does so with this short ball. It goes off the top edge towards the fine leg boundary.
On middle, blocked.
Worked with the angle, wide of mid on for one.
On off, blocked.
Good length and on off, Wagner defends it onto the ground.
Shorter and on middle, it is ducked under.
BEATEN! Fuller and outside off, Wagner looks to drive but is beaten.
Down the leg side, Wagner looks to flick but misses.
Neil Wagner walks out to bat!

OUT! DRAGS IT ON! Southee is now a goner! Joseph has another one. This is shorter and outside off, Southee plays a nothing shot. He hangs his bat out away from the body. He gets an inside edge onto the stumps. Can the Windies keep New Zealand below 380?
FOUR! Up and over! Joseph goes full and Southee lofts him over his head and bags a boundary.
Worked with the angle towards square leg for one.
A single as this is pushed towards cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, defended.
Shorter and around off, it is pushed towards cover for one.
FOUR! On the pads and Southee just uses the pace. He works it through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the fence.
A leave to end the over as this is bowled outside off.
Fuller and on middle, it is driven down the ground. The fielder at mid off dives and makes a good stop. Only one.
On the pads, Nicholls looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It lobs on the leg side for one. Leg bye.
FIVE WIDES! Way too short and it goes over the batter's head and over the hand of the leaping keeper for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Nicholls loves it there! It is full and on the pads, Henry works it through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the fence.
OHH! Length and around off, it comes back in. Nicholls use to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A dot to end! On off, blocked.
BEATEN! Length and around off, Southee looks to defend but is beaten as the ball moves away a touch.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Good length and on off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
From wide of the crease and bowled on middle, defended nicely.
On middle, defended.
Length and on off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Tim Southee walks out to bat!

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The Windies finally hang onto one and it is their skipper who shows the other fielders as to how to do it. Joseph is got on and he gets the breakthrough. He bowls it just behind a driving length outside off. Jamieson looks to push at it but does so ahead of his body. It goes off the outside edge and Holder takes a good catch to his left. Windies will now want to take the remaining three quickly.
Outside off left, alone.
Shorter and on the body, this is pulled down towards deep square leg for one. Fifty stand up. Another good stand for the Kiwis.

DRINKS! So no success for the Windies in the first hour of play and it is the Kiwis who continue to dominate. Holder did create a chance but Campbell put Jamieson down. They need to break this stand or the two will probably take the game away from the Windies.
On middle, it is driven to mid on.
On off, kept out.

A huge appeal from Bravo but he is the only one doing so! Length and outside off, Kyle looks to defend but then pulls his bat back. There is a sound when the ball pases the bat but there is a big gap between ball and bat.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, it is once again kept out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
On middle, it is pushed towards mid on for one.
Goes around the wicket and bangs it short. Jamieson defends it.
A short one, it is ducked under. Holder has overstepped.
Fuller and on off, it is driven towards mid off for one.
Outside off, left alone.
A good leave to end! Just outside off, not played at. End of an over which could have had a wicket in it.
FOUR! Shot! This time there is good amount of width on offer. Jamieson stands tall and guides it through point. It races away to the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked.

DROPPED! John Campbell is the culprit! That was a regulation catch. Should have been taken! Shorter and outside off, Kyle pushes at it away from the body. It goes off the outside edge towards second slip who spills it. If Windies keep dropping such chances, they are going to be put in deeper trouble.
On off, it is guided to point.
Length and around off, this is guided to point.
One more ball outside off, Nicholls does not play at it.
Angled into the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, this time Nicholls is in two minds whether to leave it or play it. In the end, he looks to leave it but the ball hits the bat and falls beside him.
Outside off, this is guided to point.
On off, it is pushed to mid off.

NOT OUT! It indeed is! Kyle is a tall man and it has hit him over the flap of the pad. Windies lose a review and this was probably taken more in desperation. It is angled into the pads, Jamieson looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads. An appeal but turned down. Holder reviews but replays show that the on-field call is the right one.
Review time! An appeal for an LBW has been turned down! Holder reviews. It seems to be going over though.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone again.
On off, blocked.
Outside off, not played at.
A little too straight, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, it is dropped towards cover for one.
FOUR! On the up! A very confident stroke by Kyle! Length and around off, it is stroked on the up through covers for a boundary.
On the off pole, defended nicely.
Quick single! On off, it is pushed towards mid off and Nicholls takes off. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Henry would have made it in with a dive.
On middle, defended.
BEATEN! Once again it goes over the stumps. On a length and around off, it comes in with the angle. Kyle is late in getting his bat down. The ball to his luck goes over the stumps.
On middle, this is driven towards the mid on fielder.
Slashes and misses! Shorter and outside off, Jamieson throws his bat at it but misses.
Shorter and on middle, ducked under.
Fullish and on off, Jamieson strokes it to mid off.
Slightly fuller again and on off, Nicholls drives it to mid off.
Good length and on off, defended nicely.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid off.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, this is driven back towards the bowler who deflects it back onto the stumps at his end but Nicholls is well in.
No run.
FOUR! Edgy again! This is shorter and outside off, Nicholls slashes at it. He does not get on top of the bounce and hence, it flies off the edge and over gully for another boundary.
Shorter and outside off, Henry cuts but the fielder at point dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Fuller and on middle, it is worked to square leg.
Outside off again, this is not played at.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Lucky boundary! This is on off, Nicholls is slightly late in getting his bat down. It goes off the inside edge and over the stumps to the fine leg boundary. Nicholls continues to ride his luck even today.
Angled into the middle pole, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, it is solidly defended.
On middle, it is pushed to mid on.
Good length and on off, Jamieson stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked towards square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
That has gone over the stumps! Good length and around off, it comes in with the angle. Kyle ends up playing outside the line. It goes past the inside edge and over the off pole.
Short again, it is ducked under.
Shorter and on middle, it is ducked under.
Good length and on off, Jamieson guides it to point.
Outside off again, this is not fiddled with.
Outside off, left alone.

That was a bad call for a run! Kyle should have been a goner! He pushes this full ball straight to Gabriel at mid on and takes off. Kyle knew halfway down the wicket that he is a goner. Gabriel though misses his underarm through at the stumps at the bowler's end. He had more time than he thought. Gabriel should have taken aim and then had a shy.
Just outside off, Kyle initially thinks of playing at it but then lets it go.
On off, defennded.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to extra cover. Another brilliant stroke. This time for no runs.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! What a shot that is! Wow! This is on a length and around off, Kyle strokes it on the up and through mid off. Races away.
Chemar Holder to bowl from the other end!
Outside off, not played at. Good start for New Zealand.

FOUR! Crisp! That is brilliantly timed! Nicholls begins from where he left off yesterday! This is full and on the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence. 300 up in style.
Three! Excellent running! Gabriel is not happy! This is fuller and on middle, it is driven through mid on. Chase gives it a chase but he is quite slow as he runs after the ball. Three taken.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
On middle, Jamieson gets right behind the line and blocks it.
Outside off, left alone.
We are all set for the action to begin! Henry Nicholls and Kyle Jamieson will continue. Shannon Gabriel to bowl. Here we go...

Welcome to the coverage of Day 2 of the second Test between New Zealand and Windies. It is the hosts who have their noses in front after a brilliant ton by Nicholls. 350 is what they will be aiming for from here and that should be a very good score on this wicket. Windies on the other hand, need to take the remaining wickets as quickly as possible. They will somehow have to keep the Kiwis under 350 as this already seems a total which is above par. Will we see them fightback or will it be the hosts who would continue to dominate?
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

So, one just gets the feeling that the Kiwis already have a total which is above par on this wicket. They are still not done and will be eyeing the 350-run mark atleast from here. The Windies need to keep them to below that or it is going to be an uphill task for them to come back in this game. So join us for Day 2 at 1100 local (2200 GMT, THE PREVIOUS DAY). Until then, cheers and take care.

The Windies bowling was top notch in the first session. It was good in the second as well but their fielders let them down. In the third, they were extremely poor. Holder and Gabriel were the pick but Jason and Joseph disappointed. Overall, the Windies skipper will not be happy with where they stand in the game at the moment.

New Zealand’s hero has to be Henry Nicholls. Yes, he has played with some luck but that’s what you need on a wicket which has so much on offer for the pacers. He along with Young, Watling and Mitchell have taken the Kiwis to safer shores.

New Zealand’s day in the end! The Windies have let it slip away from them after a brilliant first session. They were quite shabby in the field and their bowling too in the next two wasn’t that great which has seen the honors of the day shift towards the hosts.
Short of a length ball on off, Henry is solid in his defense. NEW ZEALAND END WITH 294/6 AT STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Back of a length ball on off, Henry blocks this one out well.
On off, blocked.
Outside off, left alone by Henry.
FOUR! Holder strays and bowls this one the pads of Nicholls, he flicks it nice into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On the pads, tucked to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length on off, Henry pushes this to the leg side.
On off, pushed to covers.
BYE! Slipped down the leg side, Jamieson looks to tuck but misses. The keeper fumbles allowing the bye to be taken.
Back of a length on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for just one.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length outside off, Henry looks to block but misses.
On off, guided to point.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Kyle leaves it alone again.
Another ball outside off, another leave by Kyle.
Outside off, left alone.
West Indies have decided to take the new ball now.
Back of a length ball on middle, tucked to the leg side for a single.
Kyle Jamieson is the new man in.

OUT! LBW! Chemar Holder has his man and he gets rid of Mitchell! A wicket that West Indies desperately needed as the Kiwis and this partnership was running away with the game! A good length ball on off and middle, Mitchell looks for the flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The players appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Both the batters indulge and then go for the review. Ultra Edge shows nothing. Ball Tracker comes in and the wickets are clipping. This stand is broken as Mitchell has to walk back now.
New Zealand review! Mitchell takes this LBW decision upstairs. Let's see what the replays have to say.
Back of a length on off, Henry tucks this to square leg for a single.
Length ball on off, Henry is solid in his defense.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on off, Henry pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out well.
On off, defended.
Floated on off, Mitchell pushes this to covers.
On off, DM blocks.
Short on middle, tucked to the leg side.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
On middle, pushed to the mid on region.
On middle, clipped to fine leg for a couple. Good running by these two.
On off, Nicholls pushes it to point.
Outside off, HN sways away and leaves it.
EDGY FOUR! On a good length on off, it goes off Henry's outside edge and goes to the third man boundary.
On off, well kept out.
Length on off, pushed to the mid off region.
Outside off and short, cut away to deep point for a single.
Floated on off, swept to the fine leg region for a brace.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Henry defends this one out.
On the pads, tucked to short fine leg for a single.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
On off, driven to mid off.
On off, blocked.

CENTURY FOR HENRY NICHOLLS! Brilliant batting by Nicholls! Test century number 6 for Henry and this one was well deserved! A girtty innings by him so far and the Kiwis will want him to continue. On a good length on off, Nicholls looks to flick but it takes the outside edge and flies past the point region and the batters collect a couple. This is an innings who could pave the way for where this game could be heading. 100 centuries overall in Basin Reserve as well.
Outside off, left alone by Nicholls. Nervy moments for Henry right now.
On off, punched to the cover region.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a good length on off, tailing away from the left-hander, Nicholls looks to drive but misses it.
On off, defended back out.
On off, tucked to wide long on for a couple.
On off, swept to the leg side for one more. 99 now.
Floated on off, Mitchell looks to sweep this one but it goes off the top edge over the first slip. A single.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
Flatter around off, cut away to deep point for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
A single! Back of a length on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for one. Moves to 97 now.
On off, blocked.
BEATEN! Wonderful bowling! Back of a length ball on off, nipping away slightly, Henry looks to block this one out but misses.
Full length delivery on off, Henry drives this to mid off.
Full ball on middle, worked to the leg side.
Loopy on off, driven to long off for a single.
On middle, tucked to square leg for one. They think about the second but Mitchell slips and this will only be a single.
On off, blocked to the off side.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter on middle, pushed to the leg side.
On middle, tucked to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Moves to 95 now! Back of a length ball on middle, Nicholls clips this one fine off his hips to deep square leg for a boundary.
On off, blocked out.

Overthrows and three runs! On a good length on off, Mitchell pushes it to the leg side and takes off for the single. The fielder has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. There was no one backing up and so the batters pick up 2 more runs. So, three runs in total.
Good length on the off pole, driven to the man at mid off.
On off, Daryl pushes this to mid off.
Back of a length on off, Mitchell pulls it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! No one is going to stop this one! Henry Nicholls moves into the 90s now! Floated on middle, Nicholls drives this one through mid on for a boundary. Getting closer to his century now.
Tosses it up nicely and lands it around off, Mitchell pushes this towards cover-point for a quick run.
Floated on off, Daryl defends this one.
On off, blocked.
Short and around off, HN punches this one through deep covers for one. The fifty run stand is also up for these two, comes off 82 balls.
Flatter on middle, tucked to square leg for a single.
On middle, blocked to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on off, tapped to point.
FOUR! He loves playing that pull shot! On a shortish length on middle, he keeps his eye on the ball and pulls this one to deep square leg for a boundary. 250 up for the Kiwis as well.
On middle, tucked behind square on the leg side for a single.
A full ball on off, HN works it towards mid on where the fielder fumbles allowing the batters a single.
Full toss on off, Mitchell plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter on off, Mitchell punches this back to the bowler.
Loopy on middle, Daryl blocks this one off his front foot.
On off, defended.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
FOUR! See you later says Mitchell! Lovely intent from Mitchell! Floated on off, Daryl drives this one through the mid off region for a boundary.
On the pads, flicked to square leg to rotate the strike.
On off, blocked off by Daryl.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Mitchell is looking good! On a good length on off, Mitchell creams his drive through the cover region to find the ropes.
A full ball on off, Darly digs this one out.
Outside off, Daryl shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, driven through mid on for a single.
Flighted on off, kept out.
FOUR! Doing what he does best! Playing his natural game! Loopy on middle, Mitchell powers this one over mid-wicket again for a boundary.
On off, defended back onto the pitch.
Flatter on off, Daryl punches this one off his back foot through covers for a couple.
FOUR! A little example of what Mitchell is capable of doing! Floated on middle, Daryl lofts this one over the mid-wicket region and will get a boundary for his efforts.
Floated on off, blocked.
Outside off, HN looks for the cut but misses it altogether.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Nicholls moves onto 80 with that stroke! In the gap again! Back of a length on off, Nicholls guides it in between the slip cordon and gully for a boundary.
Short of a length ball on off, Henry pushes this to the cover region.
Good length ball on middle, tucked to short mid-wicket.
On middle, tucked to the leg side for a single.

DRINKS! Another start of a session where the hosts have done well and are on top. They started off well with Nicholls and Watling but then West Indies did well and scalped the wicket of Watling, which was well deserved for all their efforts. The Kiwis are still doing well to add runs to the board while the visitors need a couple of quick wickets.
On off, defended out well by Henry.
Short and on middle, tucked off the back foot towards square leg for a single run.
Short and around off, cut away to deep covers for a single.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flighted on off, Mitchell paddles this around the corner towards fine leg for a single.
Floated on middle, tucked to the leg side.
Outside off again, Henry shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.

Three now! Back of a length and outside off, Mitchell gets on top of the bounce and slams this through point. Chase gives it a chase and stops it but the batters pick up three runs easily.
On the pads, DM looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Mitchell tucks this to the square leg region and is quick to say no to the single.
Loopy on off, Nicholls drives this wide of the long off region. They pick up two runs easily.
Short around off, Henry blocks this off his back foot.
Flatter on off, Henry pushes it to point.

On off, blocked towards mid on.

Down the leg side, Darly looks to flick but misses.
On middle, tucked to the leg side for a single.
Shannon Gabriel is back on. 14-5-38-3 so far.
On off, blocked.

An appeal for caught behind but no says the umpire! On a good length on off, Mitchell looks to block but misses and the ball goes to the keeper. The players appeal loudly and the umpire says nothing doing. The keeper is heard saying that the sound could have been off the bat hitting the pad. Holder does not opt for the review.
Back of a length ball on middle, HN pulls this to deep square leg for one more single.
On middle, worked to the leg side for a single.
Length ball on middle, Darly looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and goes towards the first slip on the bounce.
