A dot to end. A good length ball outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone. A maiden over by the skipper.
Length delivery on off, Henry fends this one out.
Another leave by Nicholls as Holder bowls this outside off on a good length.
Outside off, left alone by HN.
On off, Nicholls looks to block but it takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side.
Good length ball on off, Henry blocks this one out well.
On off, Daryl raises his blade and lets it be.
Short ball on middle, Henry pulls this to fine leg for a single.
Short ball around middle and leg, HN ducks under this one.
On middle, tucked to square leg for one.
On off, defended well by Daryl.
On off, blocked.
Outside off, cut to point.

NOT OUT! West Indies opt for the review but the decision that the on-field umpire stays on and this will remain not out. A back of a length ball down the leg side, Nicholls looks to flick but misses and the ball goes through to the keeper. He takes it and appeals loudly. The on-field umpire says no. Holder decides to take this one upstairs. The third umpire is having a look but wait... he says that they are unable to check if there was a nick or not because an earlier throw by the fielder damaged the stump mic. Will remain not out and West Indies retain their review.
Review time! West Indies go for the review to have this caught behind appeal checked upstairs. Let's see what the replays have to say.
On off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, HN looks to cut but it comes off the top part of his blade and bounces in front of the slip cordon.
Good length on off, HN looks to push this one but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, pushed to the leg side.
SLASH AND A MISS! Outside off, Mitchell looks to cut but misses.
Daryl Mitchell is the new man in.

OUT! TIMBER! DRAGGED ON! West Indies finally get the breakthrough that they were looking for! They have been toiling hard and have got the wicket that they deserve! Watling has played well so far but his stint out in the middle has been cut short by Joseph! Shortish delivery around the off pole, not a lot of room to work with but Watling decides to look to cut this one. He goes for the shot and the ball comes off the bat's inside edge and goes onto rattle the stumps behind him.
On middle, blocked.
On off, pushed to covers.

FOUR! 200 up for Kiwis! On a good length on off, Watling drives this through cover-point and the fielder chases behind it and he pulls it back with his foot. They check if this is a four and give it as one. Good effort in the deep nonetheless.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls nudges this to the leg side.
On off, kept out.
Outside off again, left alone by Henry again.
Outside the off pole, HN lets it be.
On middle, tucked to square leg for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Even if he had hit, Henry was safely in.
Outside off, BJ leaves it alone.
Good length on off, HN drives but it is straight to mid off.
On off, Nicholls is solid in his defense.
On middle, flicked to fine leg for a single. Fifty run stand up for these two as well, in 83 balls. An important stand for the Kiwis.
Back of a length ball on off, BJ pushes this to covers.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Nicholls continues on! Anything that he touches, turns to gold by the looks of things! On a good length on off, Henry looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and goes through the vacant third slip region into the third man fence for a boundary.
Outside off, HN pushes this to covers.
Full delivery around the off pole, Henry does not think twice in leaving this one alone.
Outside off, HN leaves it be.
Full ball on middle, tucked to fine leg for one.
Back of a length on the pads, tucked to square leg for a quick run. There is a misfield and they think about the second run but they decide not to in the end.
Short ball on middle, BJ ducks under this one.
Outside off, BJ looks to block but misses.
Joseph bowls a better length now! A length ball on off, nipping into the right-hander, Watling looks to defend but it takes the inside edge onto the pads and roll to the off side.
WIDE! Short ball around off, BJ leaves it alone. Wided.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Watling! Back of a length ball outside off, Watling leans back and cuts this one through backward point and it races away to the ropes. Joseph needs to find an answer now.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Just leaned into that off-drive and he gets a boundary! On a good length on off, Watling leanes forward and drives it through mid off for a boundary.
On middle, kept out towards short leg.
Outside off, left alone.
Good leave by Nicholls! Another full ball on off, Henry raises his willow and lets this one through to the keeper.
Good length on off, Henry leaves it alone.
On off, pushed back to Holder.
Outside off, HN does not want to engage.

FOUR! He finds the gap again, does Nicholls! Short ball on middle and leg, Henry swivels and pulls this one to the deep square leg region for a boundary. Probably his best pull shot in his innings so far.
On middle, BJ keeps it out. No run says Watling straightaway. A dot to end the over.
Good length ball on off, Watling keeps this one out.
SLASH AND A MISS! Back of a length ball outside off, BJ looks to cut this one away but misses it.
On off, blocked to point.
Bouncer on off, BJ sways away from this one.
FOUR! Dispatched in some fashion! An overpitched delivery on middle, Watling clips this one and it goes through mid-wicket for a boundary. A good start to the over.
Back of a length on middle, Henry hops and blocks it out.
On off, HN keeps it out well.
FOUR! Short and wide to Nicholls and he will accept this offer! Back of a length outside off, Nicholls punches this one through point and the ball will race away to the ropes.
Back of a length ball on off, HN looks to defend but it goes in between bat and pad to the keeper.
Short of a length outside off, HN pushes it towards point.
Good length on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Jason Holder to bowl from the other end.
On off, Watling blocks it out. A maiden to begin the session after Tea.
On off, defended.
Full on the pads, pushed towards mid on.
On middle, blocked to the leg side.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling! On a good length around off, nips slightly, BJ looks to block but gets beaten.
Back of a length on the pads, Watling looks to tuck it away but misses to get hit on the body.
We are back! The batters for New Zealand, Henry Nicholls and BJ Watling stride out into the middle. Alzarri Joseph will begin with the ball. Watling to face. Off we go...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

This could be a much-needed break for the visitors who can now regroup, come back out and look to attack the batters out on the crease. An interesting final session of play awaits us. Who comes out on top? Will the Kiwis assert their dominance or will the visitors come back well in the final session of the day? Join us on the other side to find out.

The bowling by the West Indies has not been bad but their work out on the field has been very poor. They have had a lot of catches come their way, but they have not done well enough to grab onto them. Their bowling also got slightly better towards the end of the session, with the new man coming into the crease. Their fielding is something that they will have to look at when they come out for session 3.

Session 2 goes the way of the hosts! They have been battling it out with Henry Nicholls and Will Young, as they did well and stuck around towards the start of session 2 and then when Young fell, BJ Watling has been going on with Nicholls by his side. Henry Nicholls has also reached his half-century and the Black Caps will be hoping for some more of his stroke-play in the final session of the day.
BEATEN! Wonderful bowling! On a good length on the off pole, Nicholls looks to block this one out but the ball zips away slightly, beating the outside edge and going to the keeper. THAT WILL BE TEA!
Short ball on middle, HN sways away, leaving it be.
Another ball outside the off channel, another instance where Nicholls leaves this one alone.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
BEATEN! On a good length on the fourth stump channel, Nicholls looks to block but gets beaten.
Outside off, HN leaves it alone.
Short ball on middle, BJ sways away from it.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed to the leg side.
On middle, BJ pushes it to mid on. No run is the call straightaway by Watling.
Back of a length on middle and leg, tucked to the leg side.
Full and on off, BJ pushes this to the covers.
Back of a length on off, BJ defends it to point.
On off, blocked.
Short of a length on the pads, Henry hops and tucks this to square leg.
On off, HN looks to defend but gets beaten.
Full and around off, pushed to the cover region for a couple.
On off, nudged to the leg side for one.
FOUR! Shouts of catch it but it goes away to the ropes! A full ball on the pads, Watling tickles this one and it goes past the keeper into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
A couple now! Full on middle, HN knocks it towards mid on where the fielder fumbles allowing the batters to pick up a couple.
Length ball outside off, HN leaves it.
Good length ball on off, Watling pushes it towards covers for one.
WIDE! Way outside the tramline, BJ leaves it alone. Wided.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Well played! An overpitched ball on off, Watling drives it through the carpet, past mid off and into the ropes.
On off, blocked.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR NICHOLLS! A well deserved one by Henry! A gutsy innings, has not been easy for him out there! Full on the pads, Nicholls tucks this through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the ropes. The Kiwis will be banking on him to stay out there for as long as he can.
Full and around off, pushed to point.
Full and on middle, kept out to short leg.
Back of a length ball on off, Watling defends this one out.
Good length on off, Watling blocks.
Outside off, Watling sways away and leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.

DROPPED AGAIN! A couple taken also! What are you doing, West Indies? You've got to take these chances when they come your way! On a good length on off, Nicholls looks to block this one out but it takes the outside edge and goes towards the first slip. Bravo looks to take this catch but it goes off his arms towards the third man region. Should have been taken, this. These chances might come back and haunt the West Indies later on in the game.
On a good length on off, Henry looks to block but is beaten.
Good length ball on off, Henry is quick to block this one out.
On off, played to the off side.
On off, pushed towards mid on.
On middle, pushed to the leg side. A good over for Gabriel.
On off, blocked.
Length ball down the leg side, Watling leaves it alone.
Short ball around off, Watling pushes this towards gully.
Full ball on middle, Watling looks to flick but ends up defending this out on the turf.
BJ Watling is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time, a catch is finally taken! It is the skipper this time who takes a stunning catch! Also, 150 Test wickets for Shannon Gabriel and a brilliant catch to get his 150th wicket. A length ball around off, Young looks to defend this one out but it takes the outside edge and flies towards the right of second slip. The skipper, Jason Holder is the man there. He does wonderfully well to dive to his left, get low and grab this one. A great catch and a well deserved wicket for Gabriel. The 70-run stand is finally broken and West Indies get some success after Lunch for all their toiling.
Very full on middle, worked to the short mid-wicket region for a single.
Outside off, Will raises his blade and leaves it alone.
Short of a length ball on middle, Will pulls to deep square leg for a couple.
On off, pushed to point.
On off, blocked towards the covers.
Outside off, Young does not engage.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, pushed to the leg side.

Dropped again? The keeper this time! Gabriel cannot believe what is going on and so can't we! Two catches in one over and not one of those chances are taken! Fullish ball around off, Henry looks to block this one out but misses and the ball goes to the keeper who spills this one. Holder also thinks about reviewing for the LBW appeal as it looked like it clipped his thigh pad but does not. Replays roll in and it shows it went past the outside edge. Regulation catch, that, even though there might not have been an edge there.
Outside off, pushed to point. Henry is quick to say no to the single.

DROPPED! Oh my Darren Bravo, what have you done? That should have been the fourth wicket but this drop will mean that Nicholls survives again. Gabriel is not at all happy and rightly so. He bowls a back of a length ball on off, Nicholls looks to defend but the ball nips away, kisses the bat's outside edge and goes to first slip where Bravo is waiting. He gets low to catch this one but it pops out.
LEG BYE! A short length ball on middle, Young looks to sway away but the ball hits his back and goes to the leg side. The batters collect a leg bye.
A dot to end! A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Henry looks to play at this but misses to get hit on the pads.
Another couple! A full ball on middle, Nicholls tucks this to the deep square leg region for a couple.
Good length ball around the fourth stump channel, Nicholls is solid in his defense.
Shortish ball on the body, Henry blocks this one out.
A full ball on middle, Henry blocks this one out.
Back of a length ball on off, Young looks to push at this but it takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps to the fine leg region for a single.

An appeal for caught behind but no says the umpire! Not a lot of the Windies players thought this would be out as well as there were not a lot of appeals. A back of a length ball outside off, Nicholls looks to slash at this. The ball goes through to the keeper. Some players appeal but no says the umpire. Holder smiles and declines the review on this occasion.
Another good length ball outside off, Henry watchfully leaves it alone.
A length ball outside off, Nicholls doesn't want to play at that.
On middle, pushed to the leg side.
BEAUTY! Great bowling by Gabriel! Slants this across the left-hander on a good length, nipping away slightly, Henry looks to defend but gets beaten.
Good length ball on middle, clipped towards square leg for a single. Will moves to 39.
Outside off, Henry leaves it be.
Full, on middle, blocked towards mid on.
A couple this time! A short ball on middle, Henry pulls this to mid-wicket and picks up a couple.
Outside off, Nicholls does not want to engage with this one.
FOUR! Nicholls moves into the 40s with this shot! He has been looking good so far! A full ball on middle, Nicholls tucks this one through mid-wicket and it runs away to the fence.
Down the leg side, Henry looks to flick but misses.

DRINKS! It has been all New Zealand since the Lunch break. Nicholls and Young have done well to keep the scoreboard ticking while also doing well to not lose their wicket. West Indies, on the other hand, will be hoping to get rid of one of these two and apply some more pressure on the batters of the Kiwis.
Short ball on middle, Henry pulls this to deep square leg for one.
On the pads, pushed to the leg side.
That could have hurt! A back of a length ball on the pads, Henry looks to tuck this away but misses to get hit on the body.

Two this time! A short ball on middle, Nicholls looks to pull but it takes the top half of the blade and goes towards mid on and lands safely. The batters come back for the second and the fielder cleans up and throws this to the keeper, who whips the bails off. But the batter was in safely. Will be two runs.
Very full and on off, Henry digs this one out back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Henry.
Shannon Gabriel is back on. 9-3-29-2 are his figures so far.
On off, Young looks to block but it takes the gloves and goes to the slip cordon on the bounce.
A bumper outside off, Young leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on off, Will blocks it out.
On off, pushed to the cover region for one.

SIX! Pulled away and pulled away for a biggie! Just over the man in the deep as well! A short ball on middle, Nicholls looks to pull but it takes the top edge and flies to the fine leg region. Blackwood is the man in the deep, he runs forward looking for the catch but he does not judge this correctly and it crosses the ropes for a biggie. 50 run stand up between this too as well.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls raises his blade and leaves it alone.
Short ball on middle, Henry pulls this to the fine leg region for one.
Good length on middle, Young tucks it to the fine leg region for a single.
On middle, blocked.
Good length on off, Young tucks this to the square leg region.
Outside off again, Young shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.

An appeal for LBW but it is turned down! A length ball on off, Henry looks to leave but gets hit high on the pads. The players appeal but nothing from the umpire. Holder thinks about the review but decides not to take it in the end.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
WIDE! A short ball on middle, Henry leaves it alone. Wided.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
Some bounce, this! A back of a length ball on middle, Henry thinks about defending this but the bounce gets too big on him and he leaves this and lets it go to the keeper.
Bumper! A short ball on middle, Henry sways away and leaves it alone.
On middle, tucked to the leg side for a single.
Down the leg side, Henry looks to flick but misses.
On off, Henry looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and bounces before going to the slip cordon.
Full delivery on middle, Young flicks this to the deep square leg region for a single.
On middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
On the pads, tucked to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.

An appeal for caught behind but it is turned down! Back of a length ball down the leg side, Young looks to tuck this one but misses. The keeper collects the ball. Holder appeals but no says the umpire. They discuss if they want to take the review but they do not take it in the end. A good call as replays show that the ball was nowhere near the bat as the ball passed through.
Outside off, Young shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Wonderful bowling by Joseph! A good length ball on off, Young looks to defend but it beaten.
Outside off, Young raises his bat and leaves it alone.
EDGY! A good length ball on off, Young looks to flick but it takes the outside edge and goes to the off side. Good start to the over from Alzarri.
BEAUTY! Peach of a delivery from Joseph! Away movement noticed. A full length ball on the off stump, nips away slightly as Young looks to defend and he is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, Henry leaves it alone.

FOUR! Henry got some width and he attacks this one! Back of a length outside off, Nicholls rides the bounce and slashes this one past the fielder at backward point and it runs away to the ropes. Just past the man there.
On middle, blocked.
Outside off again, left alone again.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Young got lucky! Back of a length outside off, Young looks to push this to the off side but it takes the outside edge and goes through the vacant third slip region to the third man boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on middle, Young looks to block this out but it goes off the glove and goes to the slip cordon, safely. A dot.
A couple this time! A full length delivery on middle, Young clips this through square leg and collects a brace.
A full length ball outside off, Will shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Henry tickles this to the deep square leg region for one.
Outside off, Young looks to have a poke at this but misses it.
EDGY! A full ball on middle, Young looks to flick but it comes off the outside edge and goes to the off side.
Outside off, the batters decides to leave it alone.
LEG BYE! On the pads, Nicholls looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off his pads to the leg side. A leg bye is collected.
Outside off, left alone.
Full length ball outside off, Henry leaves this alone.
On the pads, tucked to the leg side for one.

DROPPED! The man drops this one! It should have stuck onto him but it does not and Nicholls survives! A full ball on the pads, Henry flicks this to Shamarh at short leg. He does get his hands on this but then spills it. Should have taken it.
A full length delivery on the pads, Will tickles this to the fine leg region for a single.
A back of a length ball on off, Young sways away and leaves it alone.
Another short delivery on middle, Henry pulls this to the fine leg region for one.
FOUR! That sounded very good and the result too is very good! A short ball on middle, Nicholls swivels and pulls this one to the deep square leg region for a boundary. 100 up for the Kiwis as well.
LEG BYE! On the pads, Henry looks to flick but misses and this goes off his pads to the fine leg region. A leg bye is picked up.
FOUR! A beautiful stroke! On a good length outside off, Nicholls drives it through covers, and even though a fielder gave it a chase, the ball beats him to the ropes.
On middle, blocked out.
A full ball on middle, Young looks to flick but closes the face of his bat early and it takes the edge and goes to the cover region and the batters pick up a single.
Another length delivery outside off, Young decides to leave this one alone.
On a good length outside off, Young lets this one be.
Back of a length again and on off, it is pushed towards cover.
Back of a length and on middle, Nicholls defends it onto the ground.
A sharp bumper, Nicholls spots it late but does well to evade it.
FOUR! Just a push! Fuller and around off, Nicholls nicely uses the pace and strokes it past mid off for a boundary.

That is a tight leave! Not sure if Nicholls expected it to go so close past the off pole! This sgtarts outside off and then comes back in late. Nicholls leaves it. The ball goes nice and close past the off pole.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, defended nicely.
A full toss well wide outside off, it is driven through covers. It is off the toe-end and hence, does not go to the boundary. Three.
A little too straight and it is worked through mid-wicket for two.
One more ball outside off, it is left alone nicely.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
Jason Holder to bowl from the other end!

In the air... safe! Fortune favoring Nicholls. Almost the perfect start for the Windies after the break! This is short and outside off, Nicholls looks to drag the pull but it goes off the top edge and lobs on the leg side. The keeper goes after it but can't get to it. A single taken. The line on the bumper was key there. It was outside off and angling away. Nicholls had to drag it and that almost got about his downfall.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, it is worked fine. Catch it is the call but it is well wide of the keeper and it goes down to fine leg for the first run of this session.
Gets it right this time! On a length and around off, defended.
That was nippy! The line though was a little too straight. Young does not pick it up and it hits him on the body.
Starts off with one on the pads, Young looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
We are back! The Windies players have made their way out to the middle and so have Young and Nicholls. Alzarri Joseph to begin and he will be bowling to Young. Here we go...
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

New Zealand on the other hand, need a partnership. Young has a chance to prove his mettle. He has got his eye in and the Kiwis would hope he along with Nicholls can bat for long. Is there a fightback in store or will the Windies continue to dominate? Do join us in a bit to find out.

It was Gabriel who got Blundell early. There was a decent stand between Latham and Young but Holder, the debutant, got the Kiwi skipper. Jason then got Gabriel on for Taylor and the former got the job done for his skipper. Things have gone as the Windies would have wanted and more of the same is what they would want after the break.

A very good session for the Windies! Unlike the last game, Holder will be very pleased with how they have performed after he elected to bowl. They did not start off all that well though as they leaked runs early on. Once they found their lengths though, they started creating problems.
A harmless delivery to end the first session! Full and outside off, left alone. THAT WILL BE LUNCH!
Unplayable! Length and on off, it pitches and then moves away. Beats the outside edge of Nicholls' bat. Henry can't do a lot there but just hope it does not take the edge.
A full toss now on off, Nicholls strokes it back to the bowler.
On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
On the pads, Young looks to flick but misses.
Some inswing but this is down the leg side.
A little too straight, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Hitting the bat hard! Bends his bat on this one and bangs it on a length, defends it.
Excellent carry! Length and outside off, left alone. The keeper takes it near his chest.
Shorter and around off, Nicholls stands tall and defends it. This was bowled from over the wicket.
HN is underway! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for two.
Outside off, comes back in, Young leaves it. Keeps swinging as it passes the batter. The keeper makes a half stop. A single. Bye.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to extra cover. End of a wicket taking over.
Well wide outside off, left alone.
A yorker on off, Nicholls jams it out towards the bowler.
Nicholls walks out to bat! Not a lot of time to go for Lunch. Not a good time to bat at the moment.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Taylor is out of here and the reason to get on Gabriel has succeeded. He is elated. Taylor's difficult stay comes to an end. This is another beauty! It is angled into the middle pole, pitches and then leaves the batter. Taylor plays inside the line. It goes off the outside edge and the keeper makes no mistake. The big fish is a goner. Can Windies get another one before the break? They surely will if they bowll like this.
Slightly fuller and around off, Taylor plays at it with no foot movement at all. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On the pads, Young looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side for one. Leg bye.
Angled into the pads, this is worked towards fine leg for one.
Full and outside off, Young goes for the booming drive but does not time it. It goes through covers for two.
On off, blocked.
Three taken! On the pads, ths is worked through mid-wicket.
FOUR! Classy! What a shot, what a response! It is fuller and around off, Taylor creams it through covers and it races away. This should make him feel a lot better.
Taylor cops another blow! This time around the crouch! This is on a length and around off, it comes back in at pace. Taylor looks to keep it out but misses to get hit near the box.
A good bumper to end a challenging over by Gabriel. It is ducked under.
Good length and on off, Young plays it with soft hands and late towards gully.

OUCH! Another nasty delivery! This is a back of a length ball on middle, it holds its line and also takes off. Taylor looks to defend but it takes the glove and then hits the body. Rolls on the leg side for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
That took Taylor by surprise! This is short and outside off, comes back in sharply. Taylor looks to cut but gets an inside edge onto the body.
Down the leg side, Ross looks to flick but misses.
Shannon Gabriel is back on! Holder wants Taylor early and he gets his spearhead.
A single now as this is worked towards square leg. Taylor is off the mark.
On the pads, Young looks to work it on the leg side. It hits him high on the pads and rolls on the leg side for one. Leg bye.
Extra bounce this time! It is shorter and around the body. Young looks to flick but due to the extra bounce, he gets hit high on the glove.
A little too straight this time, Taylor looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes down to fine leg for one. Leg bye.
An appeal but turned down! High! Holder has his tail up here. It is on middle, there is extra bounce. Taylor looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Ross Taylor walks out to bat.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! FIRST TEST WICKET FOR HOLDER! It is of the Kiwi skipper, Tom Latham. A good wicket and this should make him feel ever so good. The two debutants combine to get that wicket. This is a lovely delivery. It is angled in on off from around the wicket. Slightly fuller, Holds its line after pitching. Latham looks to drive but does not cover for the movement. It goes off the outside edge and the keeper takes it. So once again a stand which looked promising has been cut short. Windies will look for another before Lunch.
On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
A low full toss, this is worked through mid-wicket. Gabriel at mid on jogs after it and three is taken.
Outside off, Young looks to drive but mistimes it towards cover.
Another ball outside off, not played at.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Very straight! This is really full and on middle, Young strokes it down the ground past the bowler and into the long off fence.
Comes around the wicket to end the over. It is a yorker outside off. Latham fails to jam it out.

FOUR! Holder keeps bowling it outside off, this time it is very full. Latham drives it square on the off side and bags a boundary. Jason Holder is seen encouraging his bowler. He did not mind that boundary. Probably because he got Latham to drive and that is what Holder wants.
Outside off again, this is not played at.
Good length and outside off, shapes away as it gets to the keeper. He fails to take it cleanly but no runs taken.
Full and on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
One more ball outside off, Young shoulders arms to this one.
Another leave as this is bowled outside off.
On middle, Latham is solid in defense.
Nicely played! Shorter and on off, Latham stands tall and guides it towards point. Good control on that shot.
On off, Latham stays back and defends it onto the ground.
A huge appeal from the slip cordon but the bowler is not interested. This is on middle, it is worked down to fine leg for one. 50 up for New Zealand.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on middle, defended. End of a good first over by Holder.
Outside off, left alone nicely.
On off, it is pushed towards cover for one.
One more ball on off, it is defended nicely.
Length again and outside off, left alone.
Starts off with a good length ball on off, defended. Good start.
Chemar Holder, the debutant, is on now!
This time it is an easy leave as it is well wide outside off.
Not sure what Latham was doing there! It is on a length and around leg. Latham looks to leave it but is hit on the thigh pad. He probably thought it would angle away but it came back in.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Fuller and on off, Young strokes it back towards Joseph who lets it through. One more run.
Drags his length back and corrects his line, bowls it outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Creamed! Starts off with a loosener! Full and on middle, it is driven through mid on for a boundary.

DRINKS! Decent hour of play for the Windes! They did not start all that well but have found their lengths right now. The visitors do have one but they will be eager to get another one or two before Lunch. New Zealand on the other hand, will not want to lose anymore before the break. Alzarri Joseph comes on first change.
Angled into the middle pole, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, left alone nicely.
This is worked with the angle to mid-wicket.
EDGY RUNS! Shorter and around off, Latham stands tall and looks to defend but it goes off the outer half between gull and the slip fielder for two.
On off, defended.
Another leave as it is again bowled outside off.
One more leave as this is once again bowled outside off.
Outside off, not played at.
Uppish but safe! Length and around off, Young looks to hit it on the up but it goes off the higher part, uppishly but wide of the bowler and towards mid off for two.
Outside off, left alone again.
Outside off, left alone.

That has zipped through! Almost a similar ball to the one that got Blundell. Length and outside off. Zips through and jags back in. Young is late in bringing his bat down. It hits the flap of the pad and goes to the keeper.
A single to end! On the pads, it is nudged on the leg side for one.
Angled into the middle pole, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Off the mark with a boundary! On the pads, Young works it fine on the leg side and it races away to the fence.
On middle, this is defended.
One more ball outside off, left alone again.
Once again left on length. Outside off and angling back in. Latham lets it be. It goes over the stumps.
Back of a length and around off, Latham stands tall and guides it to gully.
Outside off, Latham points the bat skywards and lets it be.
The physio is out and so is the magic spray. Latham seems fine to continue now.
OUCH! That has really hurt! Back of a length and on off, Latham looks to defend but it takes off and hits him on the arm with no protection. That is right on the elbow.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, defended nicely this time.
Another very good delivery! This one is angled in from wide of the crease. Gets it to move away late. Young is squared up as he tries to block. Beaten.
Three taken! Angled into the pads, it is worked through square leg. They take two. Young wants another, Latham is hesitant but they take it.
Good length and on off, Latham strides forward and keeps it out.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
A good follow up delivery after the wicket. It is on a length and around off, it is blocked.
Will Young walks out to bat!

OUT! TIMBER! Gabriel gets the better of Blundell once again. That is a superb delivery. Gabriel lands it just outside off and on a length. It jags back in after pitching and also skids through. Blundell is late in getting his bat down as he tries to block. The ball sneaks through and hits the middle pole. The promising opening stand has been cut short. Can Windies build on this now? Replays just shows that it went between bat and pad. Blundell was only half forward. He did not commit himself to the shot. Still though that is a superb delivery.
FOUR! Glorious! Yes, it is a half volley but still has to be put away and Blundell does so in style. He leans into it and creams it through covers. No need to run for those.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell blocks it out.
Outside off, not played at.
Extremely full and on off, Tom jams it out.
Whizzes past the outside edge! Length and outside off, Latham hangs his bat out and gets beaten. He did not need to play at that one but did have a poke at it.
Goes back to bowling length and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Just a mere push! This is fuller and around off, Holder tempts Latham to drive and Latham does so. He creams it through extra cover for a boundary.
On the off pole, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Blundell pushes it towards cover and a single is taken.
A good maiden by Gabriel. Back to back for the Windies. Outside off, just outside off. Left alone.
That is a beauty! Length and angling into the off pole. Latham has to play at it but the ball pitches and straightens. Beats the outside edge.
Length again and on middle. Latham defends it onto the ground.
Gabriel is finding his line here! On off, Latham defends it.
OHHH! That has been left on length. It is shorter and around off, comes in with the angle. Latham leaves it and it goes over the off pole. Good leave in the end.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Ends the over with one on the stumps, defended. A maiden for Holder.
Angled into the middle pole, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
BEATEN! Holder goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Gets it to straighten after pitching. Blundell looks to defend but is beaten.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Better! This one is closer to the off pole. Not close enough though to make the batter play.
Bowls this one away from Latham's strong zone but it is a harmless delivery. Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Sheer timing! Gabriel gives another gift to Latham. On the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket and it races away again. The Kiwis are off to a flier.
Three! Gabriel is not happy and rightly so. He is once again very full and outside off, it is driven through covers for three.
Gabriel goes around the wicket but bowls it on the pads again, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
FOUR! Nice and fine! This is very full and on the pads. Gabriel has not got his line right and Latham makes him pay this time. He flicks it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
One more ball down the leg side, Blundell lets it go to the keeper again. So no swing for Holder too.
Slips this one down the leg side from wide of the crease. Blundell lets it be.
Attacks the off pole this time. Blundell stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and on middle. Latham does well to nudge it around the corner for one, There was extra bounce but Latham played it really well.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Jason Holder to bowl from the other end. He will be bolwing into the wind.

FOUR! First boundary of the game! Once again it is full but there is width on offer to Blundell. He drives it square on the off side and it races away to the fence. 9 from the first over. Positive start for New Zealand.
Blundell is off the mark too! This is full and outside off, Tom leans into it and hits it through covers for a couple. So Windies are going full but the line is not right as of now.
A little too straight again, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
New Zealand and Latham both are underway! On middle, this is worked through square leg for two.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Starts off with a full toss. No swing on the first ball. It is pushed back to the bowler.

Done and dusted with the National Anthems and it is now time for the action to begin! West Indies are in a huddle and they now make their way to the middle. They are followed by the Kiwi openers Tom Latham and Tom Blundell. Shannon Gabriel, playing his 50th Test, will be starting things off for the Windies. Here we go...
Time for the National Anthems! It will the Windies who will sing first and then the Kiwis' turn.

Neil Wagner is up for an interview. He says it is a proud moment for him to play 50 Tests. States everybody has made it a special moment and he is pumped up. Adds there is not a lot of wind now but it will get windy and it is a lovely ground to play on and there is great support for them here.

NEW ZEALAND (PLAYING XI) - Tom Latham (C), Tom Blundell, Will Young, Ross Taylor, Henry Nicholls, BJ Watling (WK) (IN FOR KANE WILLIAMSON), Daryl Mitchell, Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Neil Wagner, Trent Boult.

WINDIES (PLAYING XI) - Kraigg Brathwaite, John Campbell, Darren Bravo, Jermaine Blackwood, Shamarh Brooks, Roston Chase, Jason Holder (C), Joshua Da Silva (WK) (IN FOR SHANE DOWRICH), Alzarri Joseph, Chemar Holder (IN FOR KEMAR ROACH), Shannon Gabriel.

New Zealand skipper, Tom Latham, says they wanted to bowl first but the wicket should play nicely. He is pretty excited to captain his side and he hopes they can do well. States they are quite focused on this game, it is a new day and he hopes they can do well.

Jason Holder, Windies skipper, says the wicket is pretty green and they would probably get good assistance. Mentions they did well in passage. Informs they have a couple of changes. They have had a chat about their last game and they hope they can execute the plans well.
TOSS - Windies have won the toss and have ELECTED TO BOWL!

The Windies on the other hand, have to win to avoid another series defeat. The question is, have they recovered from the drubbing they got in the first Test? They will need to put that behind and put in a strong performance here if they are to stand a chance. Stay tuned for the toss...

Hello and welcome to the coverage of the second and the final Test between the Kiwis and the Windies. A thumping win saw the hosts take an unassailable lead. Anything but a loss will see them clinch the Test series as well abs they are outright favorites to do so.

The Windies will now have to score 329 runs if they are to avoid an innings defeat! That score on this wicket, against this New Zealand bowling attack, just seems an uphill task for the visitors. It will be a magical effort and an achievement in itself if they avoid that but that seems highly unlikely. They though will be eager to show some fight and it will be interesting to see if they do fightback. The hosts would want to end this today, 10 wickets is what they need and they have more than 80 overs to go. You have to back them to end it. Can they do so? We will find out.

For New Zealand, it was only the two bowlers who did the job for them, Southee and Jamieson! Both finished with fifers and it is the very first time that two New Zealand bowlers have taken five in the same innings.

End of another poor show with the bat by the Windies. Not a lot you can write about a line-up in which only one guy managed to cross the 20-run mark and it was that man once again who has been the only Windies batter, Jermaine Blackwood. Had it not been for him, it would have been really embarrassing for the visitors. They though have one more chance now to actually show character and some fight with the willow as THE KIWIS HAVE ENFORCED THE FOLLOW-ON!

OUT! BOWLED! Southee gets his 5th wicket! Five for Jamieson and five for Tim now! Southee goes full, this is on the pads. Gabriel looks to whip it but misses to get hit on the pads. It deflects onto the stumps. WEST INDIES ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 131!
Full ball outside off, Gabriel looks to swing at it but misses it.
Full on middle, Gabriel pushes it through mid on for a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Gabriel looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. It goes towards the leg side.
Bumper on middle, Holder ducks under it.
Good length delivery outside off, Chemar lets it go.
Boult bowls a bouncer on leg, Chemar does well to duck under it.
Full delivery on off, Holder drives it through mid off for a couple.
Full on middle, Holder looks to drive but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Full delivery on off, Holder looks to drive but gets an inside edge on the pad.
On off and shapes away. Gabriel looks to defend but is beaten.
An appeal but nothing! This one is down the leg side. Gabriel looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and goes to the left of the keeper who dives and takes it.
Shannon Gabriel is the last man in.

OUT! TAKEN! There is number 9 and it has taken the Kiwis just the 16 balls to take a wicket today. Southee is the man. He gets his fourth. This is on a length and around off, shapes away late. Da Silva looks to leave it but it is a late decision as he looks to do so after looking at the swing. It goes off the bottom and to the keeper. Not a good debut for Joshua.
Just a single taken! On the pads, this is worked uppishly through square leg. There is two easily on offer but only a run is taken.
A sharp bumper, it is ducked under nicely.
Fuller and outside off, it shapes away. Left alone.
Tim Southee is back on.
Length delivery on off, Da Silva taps it to covers.
Back of a length on off, Da Silva defends it to covers.
Full delivery on the pads, Da Silva looks to flick but gets it off the pads.
Short and wide outside off, Da Silva cuts it to point.
Full on off, Da Silva drives it to covers.
Back of a length on off, Da Silva plays it to mid off.
Trent Boult to bowl from the other end!
Good length ball on off, Holder keeps it out. There was an opportunity of a run but Da Silva does not take it.
Short delivery on middle, Da Silva pulls it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length on off, Da Silva keeps it out.
NO BALL! Wagner oversteps! Length delivery on off, Da Silva blocks it well.
Good length ball on off, Da Silva defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length outside off, Da Silva leaves it alone.
Length delivery outside off, Da Silva shoulders arms to this one.

We are set to begin Day 3. The New Zealand players are out in the middle. Joshua Da Silva and Chemar Holder will resume their innings for the West Indies. Neil Wagner will start the proceedings for Day 3.

Hello and welcome to the coverage of the third day of the second Test between the Kiwis and the Windies. This game seems to be heading only one way and that is the hosts’ way. It will probably be a miracle if the Windies manage to avoid a defeat. The question here is, if given a chance, will the Kiwis enforce the follow-on? The visitors need to score another 137 runs to avoid it but that seems unlikely with two wickets in hand. Stay tuned if you want that question to be answered...
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

The hosts will hope they can come out on Day 3 and take the remaining wickets quickly. It will be interesting to see if given a chance, will they enforce the follow-on. Windies, on the other hand, have two debutants out there and they would hope the two can fight back and stay out there for as long as possible. Will that happen? Join us on Day 3 as the action begins at 1100 local (2200 GMT, THE PREVIOUS DAY). Until then, cheers and take care.

The New Zealand bowling was about two people, Southee and Jamieson. The latter is the star with a fifer and the former has the other three which has fallen. The Kiwis were on point with the ball in hand and their work in the field also was top notch as they took a couple of good catches.

The Windies were once again poor with the bat. Once again, it was only Blackwood who showed some resistance and had it not been for him, the Windies would have struggled to get to 100. Blackwood and Brooks did well after Tea, where they were solid and were making sure that they do not lose more wickets but once Brooks fell and then Blackwood followed suit, the rest of their batting just fell apart.
It has all gone brilliantly for the Kiwis. They managed to add close to 175 runs to their overnight score with Nicholls scoring a 150 and Wagner an entertaining half ton.

We really don’t think we need to mention who’s ahead in this game as the score line makes it very evident. Just like the first Test, the hosts are bossing this game too. The Windies are still a lot of runs away from avoiding the follow-on and only a miracle can help them do that.
A couple to end proceedings on day 2! A full toss on off, Holder pushes this through mid on and collects a couple before the fielder can run in and clean up. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
EDGY! On a good length outside off, Holder looks to cut this one but it goes off the under edge and goes towards Watling, who does well to dive and stop this one.
Good length ball outside off, Holder shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Yorker on middle, well dug out by Chemar.
On middle, blocked out again.
On middle, defended out onto the deck.
Good length ball on middle, Chemar works it to the leg side for one.
On middle, tickled through square leg to rotate the strike.
Yorker on off, dug out by Da Silva.
Outside off, left alone by Joshua.

NOT OUT! Impact was outside leg and hence, this will remain not out! The Kiwis were excited and went for the review but it does not work out in their favour. A full ball on middle and leg, Holder looked to flick but missed to get hit on the pads. They appeal but no says the umpire. The Black Caps take it upstairs and replays show that the impact was outside leg and so the on-field decision stays on.
New Zealand review! They want this LBW appeal taken upstairs. Let's see what the replays have to say.
EDGY! A full delivery on middle, Holder looks to flick this one but it takes the outside edge and goes through point for a couple.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
On off, pushed to the point region.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a good length on off, Holder looks to block this one out but misses it completely.
On middle, pulled to the deep square leg region for one.
Chemar Holder walks in, with his blade in hand.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and West Indies are in all sorts of trouble now! This wicket also means that Jamieson gets his 5-fer. His second one in Test cricket. What a game it has been by him so far. Joseph's small stay out in the middle comes to an end. Fullish and around off, it comes back in sharply, Joseph thinks about blocking this one out but he induces an outside edge and Watling is as safe as house.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked out.
Who is in now? Alzarri Joseph comes in.

OUT! CAUGHT! It is Jamieson again who strikes and this time he gets rid of the skipper, Jason Holder! The extra bounce takes the West Indian captain by surprise and he ends up losing his wicket! Jamieson bowls a short length ball on off, the bounce gets too big on the batter and Holder looks to pull this. He, though, does not time it well and ends up hitting it with the bottom half of the blade. It lobs towards mid-wicket where Trent Boult takes a very easy catch.
On off, pushed to point.

Good fielding in the deep! A back of a length ball on the pads, Holder hops and clips this one to the fine leg region, the fielder there runs to his right, dives and saves two runs for his side as the batters collect a couple.
Another ball outside off, Da Silva does not engage.
Good length ball outside off, Da Silva leaves this one alone.
On off, pushed towards the man at point.

An appeal for LBW but it is turned down! A back of a length ball outside off, jags back sharply into the right-hander who looks to block this one out but misses to get hit high on the pads. The players appeal but nothing from the umpire. They think about the review but do not take it in the end.
Back of a length on off, pushed to the cover region and Da Silva says a quick no to the single.
On the pads, tucked to the leg side.
On off, tapped to point.
Yorker on off, Holder does well to dig this one out.
FOUR! Good shot by Holder! A back of a length ball on middle, Holder pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Outside off, the skipper lets this one be.
Good length outside off, Holder does well in leaving this.
Outside off, left alone by Jason.
Who walks in now? The debutant, Joshua Da Silva, it is.

OUT! CAUGHT! Southee strikes and Blackwood is the man who has to walk back now! He has played really good so far but Southee makes sure that his stay out in the middle is cut short! The decision to bring on Southee pays rich dividends as he sends back the well-set batter back to the hut. Bowls it fuller and around off, Blackwood is looking for the defensive stroke but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the slip cordon where Latham again takes a good catch.
Outside off, Blackwood raises his blade and lets it through.
Good length ball on off, Blackwood looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes through gully for a couple.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
On the pads, worked to backward square leg for a single.
On off, Holder looks to block but it takes the outside edge and goes towards gully.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a good length on off, Blackwood looks to drive this one but misses.
Short and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, Holder leaves it be.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked out.
BEATEN! A good length ball on off, Holder looks to block this one out but misses it and the ball goes into the mitts of Watling.
FOUR! A good way to end the over! A short length ball on middle, Blackwood pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Shortish on leg, pulled to short fine leg.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Holder swivels and pulls this one to fine leg for a single.
Outside off, Holder raises his blade and lets this one through.
On a good length on off, Blackwood punches this one through mid on for three. 100 up for the West Indies as well.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
On off, pushed away by Jason.
BEATEN! On a good length on off, Holder looks to block this one out but misses.
On off, Holder is solid in his defense.
Good length on off, Blackwood punches this through the cover region for a single.
On off, blocked out.

An appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire! A full ball on middle, Holder looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A loud appeal but no says the umpire. There seemed to be an inside edge on this one.
Good length outside off, the skipper leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and on middle, pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, defended back on the deck.
On off, blocked.
Jason Holder is the new man in.

OUT! TIMBER! Finally, the Kiwis get the wicket! Jamieson provides the breakthrough that was so desperately needed for the Black Caps. This is a length ball on off, it nips back in sharply into the right-hander, Brooks looks to defend this one out but misses and the ball goes onto clip the top of the off stump.
LEG BYE! Good length ball on the pads, JB looks to flick but misses and the ball goes off the pads to the leg side. A leg bye is collected.
Full and outside off, JB drives it towards covers for a couple.
WIDE! Bouncer over the off stump, Blackwood leaves it alone. Wided.
Back of a length on off, Brooks fends this one out.
On off, defended back by Brooks.
On off, guided through point for a couple.
Outside off, left again by Shamarh. A maiden for Wagner.
Another good length ball outside off, Brooks is happy to see this one go to the keeper.
Well left by SB as this one was outside off again.
Outside off, Brooks raises his willow and lets it through.
Good length on off, Brooks pushes this to the point region.
Outside off, well left by Brooks.
On middle, pushed to the leg side.
On middle, well dug out by Brooks to the leg side for one.

Well played for three! Back of a length ball outside off, Blackwood rocks back and punches this through point for three as the fielder chases after this one and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
On off, pushed to the off side.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR BLACKWOOD! He has done a good job so far for the West Indies! He also reaches his fifty in a stylish manner! Back of length ball on off, Blackwood upper cuts this one to the third man region for a boundary.
FOUR! Well played by Blackwood! On a length ball on off, Blackwood creams his drive through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, punched to mid on.
Good length on off, Brooks punches this to point.

Back of a length ball on the pads, Blackwood swivels and hooks this one to the man stationed at fine leg for one. The fifty run partnership is also up for these two. A much needed one for the visitors.
On off, pushed to the mid off region.
Back of a length ball on off, Blackwood pushes this to the leg side and Brooks sends Blackwood back as he was looking for the single.
On off, blocked.
A single now! A full ball on middle, clipped to the left of square leg for a single.
On a good length outside off, Blackwood raises his blade and lets it through.
Outside off, left alone.
A full ball on off, Blackwood punches this to the cover-point region.
Full toss outside off, Blackwood pushes it to the cover region.

DRINKS! This is just what the West Indies needed. A partnership that would settle the ship for them after they got off to a terrible start. It is the duo of Blackwood and Brooks who have battled it out hard and are still out in the middle. The bowling by New Zealand, one again, has been good but they do not have a wicket to show for it. They will be looking to get one of these batters out as they are stitching a very good partnership for their side.
Back of a length ball on off, Brooks pushes this to the cover region.
Outside off, Brooks does not mind leaving this one alone.
Wagner comes around the wicket and bowls a bouncer on off, Brooks ducks under this one.
Bouncer on leg, Brooks sits under this one.
On off, blocked back towards the bowler.
Back of a length on off and middle, Brooks blocks this to the off side.
On the pads, Brooks clips this to the man at fine leg for a single.
Another ball outside off, another leave by Brooks.
Good length ball on off, Brooks looks to drive but does not connect.
Outside off, not played at.
Great bowling by Boult! A good length ball on off, Brooks looks to flick but misses and the ball goes just over the off stump into the safe hands of Watling.
Outside off, left alone by SB.
Bouncer on middle, Blackwood sits under this and watches the ball sail over him.
Short of a length on the pads again, tucked to short leg.
Straying on the pads, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Bouncer on leg, Brooks looks to pull this one but misses it completely.
Short of a length ball on off, Brooks defends this one out.
On the pads, Brooks tucks this to the man at short leg.
Full ball outside off, Blackwood raises his blade and lets it through.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! On a good length on off, JB looks to defend but it goes through in between bat and pad, just over the off stump and into the keeper's mitts.

FOUR! Welcome boundary for the visitors! Jermaine gets some width and he takes full toll of the same! A good length ball outside off, Blackwood drives this with authority through extra cover for a boundary.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Length ball outside off, Blackwood raises his willow and lets this one through to the keeper.
A back of a length ball down the leg side again, Brooks does not engage.
Outside off, not played at.
Down the leg side, SB leaves it.
Another bouncer on middle, Brooks is happy to get low and leave this one alone.
Bouncer over middle and leg, Brooks ducks under this one.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! West Indies will not care how these come as long as they do! A good length ball on the off pole, Blackwood looks to drive this one but it kisses his outside edge and flies past the third slip and races away to the third man fence.
Back of a length ball outside off, Blackwood cuts this one but finds the third slip. A dot.
Outside off, not played at by Blackwood.
A full ball on the pads, clipped to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length ball on middle, Brooks looks to flick this away but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Back of a length on middle, tucked to the square leg region again. JB looks for the single but Brooks sends him back.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
LEG BYE! Down the leg side, Brooks looks to flick but misses and this one comes off his thigh pad and rolls past the keeper towards short fine leg. A leg bye is collected.
Bouncer on middle, Brooks ducks under this one and lets it through.
Back of a length ball on off, Brooks hops and keeps this one out.
A bouncer on middle and leg, Brooks ducks under this one.
Change at both the ends as Neil Wagner takes over the bowling duties. His figures so far read 3-1-15-0.
On off, punched to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball on off and middle, Blackwood looks to flick it away but misses to get hit on the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the off side.
Outside off, Blackwood has no issues in leaving it alone.
On the pads, clipped towards fine leg to rotate the strike.
On a length on off, Brooks pushes this to the off side.
Trent Boult is back on. 6-4-8-0 are his figures so far.
Outside off, left alone by Blackwood.
A couple this time! On a length on off, Blackwood tucks this through mid-wicket to collect a couple.
On off, blocked.
Bouncer on off, Blackwood sways low and looks for the upper cut but misses it.
On off, punched to the cover region.

NOT OUT! A very smart decision by Blackwood as the review shows that the wickets were missing and he survives! A good length ball on middle and leg, nipping into the right-hander, Blackwood looks to tuck this one away but misses to get rapped on the pads. The players appeal and up goes the finger. Blackwood does not even talk to his partner and he goes for the review straightaway. Ultra Edge shows nothing. Ball Tracker comes in and the ball is missing the wickets. West Indies retain their review and the on-field decision will be reversed.
West Indies review! Blackwood is given out by the on-field umpire for this LBW appeal. He wants to verify this upstairs. Let's see what the replays have to say.
Length ball on off, Brooks defends this one out.
On off, pushed to the cover region. SB is quick to say no to the single.
Outside off, Brooks looks to block but does not connect.

First runs after what seems to be an eternity! 27 dot balls before this and now finally a run is added for the visitors! A back of a length ball on off, Blackwood looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes towards backward point. The batters take a single.
Full ball on of the off pole, Blackwood drives but finds the man at mid off.
Outside off, left alone by Jermaine.
Good length ball outside off, Brooks is happy to let this one through. Another maiden for Southee.

The West Indies are in a bit of a pickle now and are 4 wickets down. They will be looking at their remaining batters to take them to safer shores and will be hoping that they do not lose any more wickets. The Black Caps, on the other hand, will be looking to continue what they have been doing and will want to restrict the visitors to a small total. An interesting final session of play awaits.

The Kiwis lost their final two wickets after lunch and then started off on the right foot with the ball when they scalped a wicket right inside three overs. It was Southee who started getting rid of Brathwaite. It was Tim again who sent Darren Bravo back to the pavilion, taking a very good catch. Then, it was the magical first over by Jamieson in which he got two wickets on the trot and had two appeals for LBW turned down which has completely turned the tide to the hosts' favour.

Another session where the hosts have been very dominant. They have been brilliant with the bat and have continued that with the ball and the West Indies are clearly on the back foot. Their batters will need to put on a brave show if they are to steady the ship.

So, that is it from this game and this series! It was all New Zealand. The Windies have gone winless. A lot to think about for them going ahead. The Kiwis, on the other hand, are in excellent touch and will now be looking forward to the series against Pakistan. We hope you enjoyed our coverage, till next time, goodbye and take care!

Tom Latham, New Zealand skipper, says it is really nice to get the full points from this Test series. Mentions they are playing very good cricket and that is showing now. He mentions they hope they can keep going and they have another Test series which is starting in a week or so and they are looking forward for it. Also adds, Henry's innings here and Williamson's in the first Test, the bowlers have been brilliant and he hopes they can continue to do the good work. Further says the groundsmen did a great job, it is important to adapt to the surfaces and they did that.

Jason Holder, West Indies skipper, says he is disappointed to lose another Test match. Mentions the fight they showed in the second innings is what they have been wanting to do. Mentions the bowlers did really well, they created the opportunities but did not hold onto it. Adds they just have to keep going, they have showed they can do it but they need to be consistent and they need to find a way, dig deep and there is a lot to work on. Also says he expects them to play a lot better, they really let themselves down in the field in the first innings, you can't give good players chances and they need to figure out things.

Kyle Jamieson is named the Player of the Series. He says that he is just very excited to get how far he can go. Adds that he tries to improve each day and that will help his side to win games of cricket. Mentions he wants to be an all-rounder, bowling is his preference but he wants to contribute in both the departments. States playing overseas is the exciting part. Tells he wants to learn and understand how to use his skills in overseas conditions.

Henry Nicholls is named the Player of the Match. He starts by saying that he is happy with his innings. Adds that it was nice to get a great knock like this. Mentions that they built partnerships which was key for them. Nicholls also says that he credits his club for his performance.

New Zealand then enforced the follow-on and the Windies managed to show some sort of a fight in the second innings! Three of their batters managed to score fifty, Holder, Campbell and Da Silva. They came quite close to avoiding an innings defeat but a combined bowling effort from the Kiwis ensured that does not happen. Overall, a very complete performance by the Kiwis. Stay tuned for the presentation ceremony!

In reply, West Indies were bundled out for a mere 131. Only Blackwood crossed the 20 run mark. Out of the 131, he scored 69 for them. For the Kiwis, it was for the very first time two bowlers picked five each in one innings. Jamieson and Southee starred with a fifer.

The pattern of this Test was quite similar to the first game! The Kiwis were put into bat and they got to a total which was surely above par on a wicket which did have a lot in it for the bowlers. Henry Nicholls was the star for them with the bat with a brilliant ton. He did receive support from a few others but he was the mainstay for them.

Another comprehensive win for the the Kiwis! They have won both the Tests to have been played and in some style! Excellent all-round performance from them. The Windies, on the other hand, will be very disappointed with how they have performed. Not many expected them to win but the fact that they have not shown any kind of fight in both the Tests was disappointing.

The Kiwis, on the other hand, will want to avoid batting again. Their bowlers have had a full night of rest and they will be eager to get out there and take the remaining wickets as quickly as possible. Will we have another session in this game? We will find out...

Hello and welcome to what could well be the last day of this Test. The Windies have somehow managed to drag this into the 4th day with a deficit of 85. Their first aim would be to avoid innings defeat and then see where it goes from there.
... Day 4, Session 1 ...

The Windies, on the other hand, will hope they can somehow avoid an innings defeat, that will probably be the first thing they need to try to do and then see where they can take the game from there. For that, a lot will rely on the two batting out there. Can they continue the good work? We will find out. Do join us for all the action. Till then, take care and goodbye!

The New Zealand bowling was once again very impressive. This time it was Boult who was the pick for them. Kyle Jamieson was once again amongst the wickets. However, they just looked tired towards the end and understandably so. They will now get a well-deserved rest, they will hope to come back on Monday and finish the game as soon as possible.

The day though quite easily belonged to the hosts! They got the two wickets early and enforced the follow-on. The Windies batted a lot better in the second innings despite losing Bravo and Brathwaite early. Campbell and Brooks put up a good stand with the former scoring a half ton. They then lost three wickets in quick succession but Holder and Joshua have shown very good reliance to get the deficit down to 85 and take the game into Day 4.

So the inevitable has happened! STUMPS IT IS! So, just like the first Test, just as it seems like this Test will be getting over on the third day, the Windies surge a fightback, it was Jermaine Blackwood and Joseph then, it is Holder and Joshua Da Silva now. The 74-run stand means this session is won by the Windies and we will have a Day 4.

Update 1730 local (0430 GMT) - The light meter is out and the umpires feel that the light is not good enough to continue and off they go! Stay tuned for more updates. It seems highly unlikely there will be any play today. They need to be out there by 1800 local or that will be it.

We are back for the final session of Day 3. The New Zealand players are out in the middle. Jason Holder and Jermaine Blackwood will resume their innings for West Indies. Trent Boult will start the proceedings for this session.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

The Kiwis have bowled well so far, they just need to continue to be patient. Just the five wickets is what they need. Windies, on the other hand, would be eager to take this into Day 4.
